  "text": "Welcome! don't And forget to wipe your feet before you come WELCOME HOME You never forget your first nest. Your nests are tiny! It depends on your species. but most hummingbird nests are small cups about the size of a golf ball. When it comes to building nests. female hummingbirds are in complete control. Grown male hummingbirds do not build. visit. or even sleep in nests. Nests are often built on branches more than ten feet off the ground in places safe from bad weather and predators No branch nearby? Hummingbird nests can also be found inside lamps. on wires. or in any other spot that looks safe to a mama hummingbird. Your nest is made of leaves. twigs. fibers. Echens. moss. and other materials. It is held together with stretchy spider silk It takes you a few days to build a nest. Yow nest is fragile and probably wont last more than one breeding season But you might rebuild it in the same spot every year. You're handy at home! It your nest is damaged. you will uy to repair it UNDER CONSTRUCTION Nest Sweet Nast",
